openports

List all TCP sockets in LISTEN state on the local machine, showing
which process is bound to which port. Requires sudo so that sockets
owned by other users (and root-owned daemons) are visible.

Equivalent to:

  sudo lsof -iTCP -sTCP:LISTEN -n -P

`-n` suppresses host-name resolution and `-P` suppresses port-name
translation, so the output uses raw IPs and port numbers.
